FATEs_Defense_Another Round_Desc: One of Buscarron's Druthers' more unruly patrons─Spenser of the Bottomless Cup─has (once again) had one too many mugs of mead, and begun fighting with another customer. Come and silence the sot.
FATEs_Defense_Defending the Hive_Desc: Join forces with the Wood Wailers to defend Redbelly Hive from the bandits who seek to reclaim it.
FATEs_Defense_Keeping the Hive_Desc: Defend Redbelly Hive while demoralizing the remaining Redbellies by slaying their larceners.
FATEs_Gather_Hide and Seek_Desc: The Twelveswood has become a breeding ground for poachers. Slay the lawless fiends, retrieve the hides of their innocent victims, and deliver them to the Wood Wailer.
FATEs_Gather_Robbin' Goblins_Desc: Goblin robbers have attacked a merchant en route to Gridania. Cut down the culprits and reclaim the lost crates!
FATEs_Notorious monster_A Tale of Two-ta: The Sixth Astral Era airship landing ruins have been transformed by poachers into a black market. Seek out and slay their ringleader, Yabi Two-tails.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Clearing the Hiv: Make haste to the heart of Redbelly Hive and defeat the bandit leader Severaint Seven Splinter.
FATEs_Notorious monster_The Coeurl King_: A band of Miqo'te poachers has begun hunting in the Twelveswood, led by a solitary male who has crowned himself King of the Coeurlclaws. Slay the unholy sovereign and send his subjects scampering.
FATEs_Notorious monster_The Hunted_Desc: Sirocco, a giant antelope long sought after by the Trappers' League, has been sighted in the area. Fame and fortune await those who can claim this trophy.
FATEs_Notorious monster_What Gored Befor: Trained for boar fighting by a sylph elder, Phaia had not fought two battles before turning on his master and consuming him in a single bite. Now the former champion of the boar pits roams free in the wood, goring those foolish enough to stand in his way.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Breaching the Hive_De: Infiltrate Redbelly Hive by defeating the gatewatches and opening the gates.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Conspiracy Theory_Des: High-ranking members of the Redbelly Wasps have gathered in an abandoned hovel to discuss their next attack on Gridania's trade routes. See that they do not leave alive.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Eft for Dead_Desc: Black efts from the east have begun taking over Rootslake, forcing out other species native to the area. Help cull their population before it's too late.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Fate Is a Fecal Mistr: The countless steaming pools of fecal ooze left by the stropers who have invaded Rootslake since its waters were drained are making those stationed at the nearby camp sick and unfit to fight. Help is sought in clearing the area of the vined creatures in a last-ditch effort to clear the air.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Kickin' It with the K: The Upper Paths have become tangled with kedtraps. Slice your way through the seedkin before they choke the life from the forest.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Rogue on the Water_De: Once a vast lake, home to myriad wavekin, the water of Rootslake has been sucked nigh dry by rogue sprites. Cull the creatures and restore the area's aetherial balance.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Stag Parting_Desc: Something has normally placid antelope stags stirred into a frenzy. Put the poor beasts down before they injure themselves or others.
FATEs_Slay enemies_The Negotiators_Desc: Negotiations between goblin merchants and a gang of local poachers have turned sour. Use this opportunity to teach both bands of outlaws a lesson!
FATEs_Slay enemies_To Train a Tortoise_D: The ragtag band of cutthroats and thieves known collectively as the Redbelly Wasps have got it in their heads that an adamantoise might be trained to crush their enemies, and now they dart about Rootslake poking and prodding the otherwise peaceful giants into a frenzy. Cuff the troublemakers before the entire area is overrun with angry adamantoises.
FATEs_Slay enemies_To Whom the Toll Goes: Footpads have set up illegal checkpoints along major roadways, and are forcefully collecting coin from any who attempt to pass. Seek out these ne'er-do-wells and show them crime doesn't pay.
Npcyell_111_Text: Sod off, ye sack o' squirrel shite!
Npcyell_19_Text: My wares! Those damned goblins have made off with my wares!
Npcyell_58_Text: Come! The Wood Wailers seek volunteers!
